# dbx-tools-js

Bun + TypeScript monorepo for `@dbx-tools/*` AppKit add-ons targeting
Databricks Apps. Sixteen publishable packages plus a runnable demo.

## Packages

| Path | Package | Role |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `packages/shared` | `@dbx-tools/shared` | Plugin lookup, cookies, strings, logger, memoize, auth-aware REST helper, access-token scope parsing (`tokenUtils`). Browser-safe surface via `index.client.ts`. |
| `packages/sdk-shared` | `@dbx-tools/sdk-shared` | Zod schemas regenerated from Databricks SDK `.d.ts` (driven by `devkit codegen`). |
| `packages/genie-shared` | `@dbx-tools/genie-shared` | Wire-format types + `GenieChatEvent` union for Genie streaming. |
| `packages/genie` | `@dbx-tools/genie` | `genieChat` (raw) + `genieEventChat` (semantic events) drivers. |
| `packages/model-shared` | `@dbx-tools/model-shared` | Pure Model Serving capability tiers, score profile, endpoint descriptor, and tier classifier (browser-safe). |
| `packages/model` | `@dbx-tools/model` | Node-side Model Serving access: cached `/serving-endpoints` listing, fuzzy name resolution, `resolveModel`. Re-exports `model-shared`. |
| `packages/model-proxy` | `@dbx-tools/model-proxy` | OpenAI-compatible local proxy (`model-proxy` bin) over Databricks Model Serving, with auth + fuzzy model-name resolution via `@dbx-tools/model`. |
| `packages/appkit-config` | `@dbx-tools/appkit-config` | `createApp` wrapper that auto-configures capabilities (e.g. `autopg()` Lakebase env) before delegating to AppKit's `createApp`. |
| `packages/appkit-mastra` | `@dbx-tools/appkit-mastra` | AppKit plugin that mounts Mastra agents + chat route + Lakebase memory. Per-request Databricks workspace with Assistant skills from `/Workspace/.assistant/skills`. |
| `packages/appkit-mastra-shared` | `@dbx-tools/appkit-mastra-shared` | Dependency-free wire-format contract + URL helpers + Genie writer-event vocabulary. |
| `packages/appkit-mastra-ui` | `@dbx-tools/appkit-mastra-ui` | React chat UI for the Mastra plugin (`./react` + `./styles.css`, AppKit-token styled). `MastraChat` drop-in + controlled `ChatView`. |
| `packages/appkit-email` | `@dbx-tools/appkit-email` | AppKit `email` plugin + approval-gated `send_email` Mastra tool. Sends over SMTP (sender derived from the OBO user on a configured domain), or, with no SMTP credentials, writes each email as HTML to a local outbox dir for testing. |
| `packages/appkit-email-shared` | `@dbx-tools/appkit-email-shared` | Dependency-free email message / result contract (zod schemas + inferred types). |
| `packages/appkit-email-ui` | `@dbx-tools/appkit-email-ui` | React `EmailPreview` / `EmailApprovalCard` for the `send_email` approval flow (`./react`). |
| `packages/devkit` | `@dbx-tools/devkit` | The `devkit` build/scaffold/release toolkit behind the root `build`/`typecheck`/`format`/`codegen`/`verify`/`create`/`tag`/`release` scripts. Ships a `devkit` bin + library API; reusable as a dev dependency in other Bun monorepos. |
| `packages/zerobus` | `@dbx-tools/zerobus` | Thin wrapper over the Databricks Zerobus ingest SDK. |
| `demo` | `@dbx-tools/appkit-demo` | Private runnable Databricks App that wires everything up. |

## Package shape

Capabilities follow a `<name>` / `<name>-shared` / `<name>-ui` trio
(see `appkit-mastra*`, `appkit-email*`): server logic in the plugin
package, a dependency-free wire contract in `-shared`, and React in
`-ui`. Scaffold new packages with `bun run create [--plugin|--shared]
<slug>` rather than hand-rolling `package.json` / `tsconfig`.

A `-shared` (or any) package is a **single `index.ts`** by default. Only
add the `index.ts` + `index.client.ts` browser/server split when the
package genuinely contains server-only code (a `node:*` import, even
transitive) that must be kept out of browser bundles - that is the sole
reason `@dbx-tools/shared` carries the split. A pure types / zod /
browser-safe package (e.g. `appkit-email-shared`, `appkit-mastra-shared`)
stays single-entry.

## Daily commands

```bash
bun install                 # from repo root
bun run typecheck           # bunx --bun tsc --noEmit (workspace-wide)
bun run build               # build every publishable package (tsc per pkg)
bun test                    # run bun test across all packages
bun run tag                 # patch bump + commit + push + tag + push tag
bun run --filter '@dbx-tools/appkit-demo' dev  # run the demo app
```

## Workspace plumbing

- Sibling packages depend on each other via `workspace:*`.
- Catalog dependencies (`catalog:`) are declared in the root
  `package.json`'s `catalog` field; the publish step rewrites both
  protocols to real version ranges before `npm publish`.
- All `@dbx-tools/*` packages are version-fixed via
  `.changeset/config.json` and ship together.
